on public library"], "date": "1937-09-09", "dates": ["1937-09-09"], "description": ["FINANCIAL NEWS The Business Trend Resting On Backlogs The stock market In August reg istered the largest net decline for any month since July 1934 but did not quite descend to the low of the present year Bond averages showed a smaller net loss Trading on the stock exchange was characterised by ack of vitality but a loss of 61 points in one month was sufficient to compel inquiries as to the cause For eign selling of shares anti a clouded international outlook were factors of uncertainty but there is no reason to doubt the accuracy of the New York Timess comment that con indecision of thestock market reflects above all else the mixed views with respect to the extent of the seasonal autumn pickup in in dustry and trade A number of carefully considered views afford the best opinion now available with regard to the coming months The review of the National City bank says that businessmen look forward to a good volume of trade activity in the fall but are conduct ing their affairs conservatively and there is little evidence of the boom psychology prevalent at this time a year ago The City banks summary agrees with most"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-04-13T06:41:58.789Z", "group": ["ndnp/mb", "massachusetts-boston-public-library"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83020847/1937-09-09/ed-1/?sp=13", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mb:batch_mb_basil_ver01:data:sn83020847:00517170963:1937090901:0503/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=268&w=205", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mb:batch_mb_basil_ver01:data:sn83020847:00517170963:1937090901:0503/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=537&w=410", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mb:batch_mb_basil_ver01:data:sn83020847:00517170963:1937090901:0503/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1075&w=820", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordina